washing-up bill
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a Bill presented to the House of Representatives near the end of a session containing those odds and ends of matters and legislation that need to be passed, but often cannot be fitted into other Bills (e.g. alienation of pieces of Crown land, State Forest, etc.)
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
